TEST NOTES -------------------------------------

1- Testing /projects capabilities

MM/DD/YY - 15:50
1.01 GET /projects, output the in the projects list
1.05 HEAD /projects, nothing is returned in body
1.06 POST /projects, allows to create a project without ID. Automatically generates the next available ID number (2 in this case)

2- Testing /projects/:id capabilities

MM/DD/YY - 14:01

1.02 GET /projects/1, outputs entry 1 in projects list
1.03 GET /projects/2, outputs entry 2 in projects list
1.03 GET /projects/3, outputs error (404 Not found) as expected

1.03 HEAD /projects/1, returns empty body, no error
1.03 HEAD /projects/3, returns empty body, no error handling (404 not found)

1.03 POST /projects/3, returns error message as expected

1.03 POST /projects/2, returns project 2 unchanged
1.03 POST /projects/2 with body:{"title": "project 2"}
returns project 2 with changed title
1.03 POST /projects/2 with body:{"id": "2"}, 
returns {"errorMessages": ["Failed Validation: id should be ID"]}
1.03 POST /projects/2 with input: {"title": "project 2",  "completed": true}
returns {
    "id": "2",
    "title": "project 2",
    "completed": "true",
    "active": "false",
    "description": ""
}, as expected

1.03 PUT /projects/1 with input: {"title": "project 1"}
returns {
    "id": "1",
    "title": "project 1",
    "completed": "false",
    "active": "false",
    "description": ""
} as expected

1.03 DELETE /projects/3 empty body output as expected
1.03 DELETE /projects/2, empty body output, 202 OK

